 3.4. Analysis 
 
 and there is (good) enough grazing area for herd (act of something getting bigger, wider, etc.). 
 (cows, bulls, etc.)  keeping is the major money-based business/project for 
 most of the population in the Western Area of control/area of land 
 and other choice uses for the total capital included in 
 the (related to a local area) group are not present. Neither are banks present that offer a hope of/future of real 
 positive interest rates in combination with acceptable 
 transaction cost. For these reasons the average opportunity costs of capital invested in (cows, bulls, etc.)  are set to zero. 
 The benefits can this way be attributed to the remaining 
 useful thing/valuable supply: labor. The return from keeping a cow ranges 
 from 106 to 222 K/manday from year 3 onward. To this 
 must be added the benefit received/got when the animal is 
 sold sometime within the period of 15 years. This return to labor per day is a lot above the return to 
 labor from crop production, which has been guessed 
 
 Having valued the physical production and guessed the benefits in insurance, financing, and status 
 display, the total benefit of a cow can be expressed in 
 the two indicators: the benefit came/coming from keeping 
 a cow per year; and, the benefit of selling the animal 
 at the end of the year, Table 4. The benefit received/made from 
 from keeping an animal declines after the (related to the process of making children) 
 period, but due to the benefits in insurance and status 
 display it does not become very small. The mere fact of 
 having an animal this way results in benefits. 
